  "text": "ORFs were also searched for the presence of an N-terminal signal sequence, using the signalP program (http:// www.cbs.dtu.dk/services/signalp-2.0 ; [CITATION_1] ). However, the N-terminal 100 instead of the recommended 70 amino acid residues were used, since autotransporters tend to have long signal sequences [CITATION_2] . The C-terminal 350 amino acid residues were analyzed by hand for the presence of a domain that could form a L-barrel structure [CITATION_3] . Finally, the last nine amino acid residues were compared to the signature sequence for the postulated last L-strand of the [CITATION_4] , whereby the last three residues were described as the most important [CITATION_5] . DNA and protein sequence analysis and handling were done using the ",
